"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"## The future of digital wearables\\n\\nWhile the concept of interactive digital fashion is still emerging, Kaspar believes that the wear-to-earn model will eventually be bigger than play-to-earn. Following the release of Axie Infinity, play-to-earn has [become the most popular search term](https://cointelegraph.com/press-releases/the-future-of-play-to-earn-opportunities-and-challenges) in the blockchain ecosystem.\\n\\nKaspar, however, explained that the wear-to-earn concept will undoubtedly appeal more to the mainstream — particularly women — rather than just gamers. For instance, Kaspar mentioned that digital wallets will soon resemble virtual closets, a feature that will attract many new users to the blockchain space: “Many companies are working on creating interoperable digital closets where you can move NFTs in and out of.\\\"\\n\\nAlthough innovative, Tan pointed out that online games helped inspire the rise of digital fashion:\\n\\n> “Fortnite and other online games as such created a whole new economy with brands like Balenciaga seeing the opportunity to reach out to these users in a digitally-native manner. This, coupled with the advent of COVID-19, saw more people online and exploring how they can best interact and express themselves in a digital sphere.”\",\"timestamp\":1639035018,\"title\":\"The future of digital wearables\"},\"digest\":\"C0A67Y7h6A6VxVwTuSjtJSA2jndvii__EAMi7mEv5Is\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xB9D546a28e709070a2A3125F0CcF0ef628f62C25\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"xTOmtzqC_Hkpey24SJP0LTFqHfEpkjf0WewHoPnvmi4\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"m_NKAB95Uz0LV3n840Rl4HZrJ2_MYS08dRDzWwseNEs\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"HCqcNgcJg6YEN6Hj7Dx7FwVT1fqsEgoSUltk5ZWNfzQ8TLuVFy8fhIlsZAK3P80M3PZjQaMFqNWDpy8tMOZ-Ww\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x94414fc6f7094e82c2ef231534968208ec65aa0741a45fb89461f8b8fd6e0dfe1a92d5b163d4a08c47f8cf0453774a703b0